CAM@ C43011 Nissan Cedric 130 1969 11th All Japan Stocker Fuji 300km Winner S. Suzuki

Purchased: 2014

This is the car Seiichi Suzuki drove to his 2nd Fuji "All Japan Stocker" win on May 17, 1969.

Seiichi became a Nissan works driver in 1968 and founded TOMEI as a tuning factory for race cars that same year. Seiichi's tuning business continued to grow and eventually became what is now known around the world as Tomei Powered. Click here for a group shot of all 4 racing Cedrics from CAM@.
